==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Irrespective
<hw>Ir`re*spec"tive</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧r`r⟦esl⟧*sp⟦ecr⟧k"t⟦icr⟧v)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Without regard for conditions,
circumstances, or consequences; unbiased; independent; impartial;
<as>as, an <ex>irrespective</ex> judgment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 790 --></p>

<p><q>According to this doctrine, it must be resolved wholly into the
absolute, <qex>irrespective</qex> will of God.</q>
<rj><qau>Rogers.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disrespectful.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir
C. Cornwallis.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Irrespective of</b></col>, <cd>regardless of; without
regard to; <as>as, <ex>irrespective of</ex>
differences</as>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irrespectively</ent>⟦br⟧
